fr.sii.ogham.core.resource.resolver

Class FileResolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.core.resource.resolver.AbstractPrefixedLookupPathResolver
      • fr.sii.ogham.core.resource.resolver.FileResolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RelativisableResourceResolver, ResourceResolver

    public class FileResolver
extends AbstractPrefixedLookupPathResolver
implements RelativisableResourceResolver
    Resource resolver that searches for the resource on the file system. The resource resolution can handle relative path but it depends on the runtime environment. It is better to provide an absolute path. The generated resource information will only contain a reference to the stream of the found resource. If file pointed out by the path doesn't exist, then an ResourceResolutionException is thrown to indicate that the resource couldn't be found.
